                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6">Body of Christ before burial represented
                        in the form of a cross. Each of the four cardinal points is associated with
                        a part of Christ’s body and with a personage from New Testament history. The
                        four intercardinal points are also indicated. Christ’s head and feet are
                        drawn above and below the cross (for a different representation of the same,
                        s. SSB-005, fol. 135r).
 Frontispiece miniature.</decoNote>
