               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0165DSM">Dabra Sahǝl Qǝddus Mikāʾel Bet Mäḵaʿ /
                           DSM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1841" notAfter="1852">Śahlä Dǝngǝl is mentioned as the
                        reigning monarch on <locus target="#59rb">59rb</locus>, 60va; Ṗeṭros is
                        mentioned as the Patriarch (<locus target="#44va">44va</locus>, 48vab, 61ra)
                        and salāma as the Metropolitan. Śahlä Dǝngǝl was king of Ethiopia in
                        1832-40, 1841-50, 1851-55 (with short intermissions). Peter VII was
                        Patriarch of Alexandria in 1809-52, salāma III was Metropolitan of Ethiopia
                        in 1841-67.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Additio 1 mentions ʾabbā Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer as the donor. The note also mentions
                     the names of the donor’s parents and several other relatives.</provenance></history>
